* Errors

- Go does not have exceptions
- It has error type

    type error interface {
        Error() string
    } 

- An error variable represents any *value* that can describe itself as a string

* Handling errors

- Naive approach

    fd, err := os.Open("might_error.txt")
    if err != nil {
        return err
